  "original_title": "\u0b9a\u0bbf\u0bb2\u0bbf\u0ba3\u0bcd\u0b9f\u0bb0\u0bcd \u0bb5\u0bbf\u0bb2\u0bc8\u0baf\u0bc8 \u0b89\u0baf\u0bb0\u0bcd\u0ba4\u0bcd\u0ba4\u0bc1\u0b95\u0bbf\u0bb1\u0ba4\u0bc1 \u0bb2\u0bbf\u0b9f\u0bcd\u0bb0\u0bcb",
  "text_idx": {
    "en": {
      "title": "Litro raises cylinder prices",
      "author": "unknown",
      "body_lines": [
        "Litro Gas Company has announced that it will increase the price of one gas cylinder by 50 rupees in the coming period.",
        "Mudita Peiris, Chairman of Litro Company, had already said that the price of gas cylinder should be increased by 200 rupees.",
        "However, considering the current plight of the people of the country, it has been decided to increase the price of one cylinder by Rs. 50, the company said.",
        "In this case, a ship loaded with 3,700 metric tons of gas block arrived at the port of Colombo today (10).",
        "Litro President Muditha Peiris said that they will distribute gas cylinders from tomorrow (11) and within the next two days, 140,000 gas cylinders are planned to be distributed in 140 selected places in Colombo.",
        "Meanwhile, another ship loaded with 3,700 metric tons of gas will arrive in Sri Lanka tomorrow (11), Litro said."
      ],
